author: basavaraj swamy
text:
I am sorry to say this. This man was my professor at KMC..
These are his words then.
1. Medicine changes by 8% every month. If you are not in touch with recent advances for a year, you are out of medicine.
2. While quoting an information from a journal, he use to quote the page numbers, issue number, year and name of the journal.
We thought he is a role model, and learnt the art and science of medicine and started taking care of our patients.
In the last 30 years, we have done reasonably well.
Now this man is talking very light about medical science and creating confusion among innocent patients.
Now I am coming from a funeral where I overheard that the deceased had severe hypertension and discontinued treatment after listening to B M Hegde's lectures.
Now whom to blame??
